  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I must say here a word of-- maybe coming from the wrong source, being me-- a commendation about Franco.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Franco has never handed out his Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Franco, in a silent manner, shut his eye to a lot of Jews who ran away from Belgium, Germany, Austria via France to Spain, and continued from there on either to Portugal or, or South America or wherever, and actively-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] maybe not supported it, because obviously he was an ally of Germany.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Hitler supported him in his civil war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nevertheless, being a fascist-- and whatever people say, has-- had the decency of tolerance to let Jews survive and escape via Spain.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This is an, an absolute fact.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In, in, in fact, I, I know people who, in Gibraltar-- who told me that the, the governor of Andalusia, which is a southern province of Spain, who was a general in Franco's army has actively, on Franco's say-so, assisted the Moroccan Jews' escape in 1950 via Spain.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they let them stay in temporary camps there until they went on to either Israel or France.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So one has got to give credit where it's due.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, for the Austrian Jews, I literally only know as much that the people who rented our big garage premises-- which later become-- became under Communist times, the central headquarters of the Communist party's garages-- used to go up weekly to, to, to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we, we sent to some people who we knew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We didn't know they could not have easy access to Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because the Austrians were probably the worst anti-Semites.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
